---
title: One-Pan Shawarma-Spiced Chicken & Rice with Golden Raisins, Carrots & Cilantro Crema
description: When you picture shawarma, do you imagine chicken on a stick? Tonight’s spiced chicken has all the typical Middle Eastern-inspired flavors, but it’s cooked in one pan. You’ll add carrots, garlic, rice, and raisins to your chicken, then mix it all together with a squeeze of fresh lemon, a drizzle of cilantro crema, and a garnish of almonds. Ditch the rotisserie for a dinner that’s easy to clean up and even easier to gobble down.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-shawarma-spiced-chicken-rice-c8bc9870.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-shawarma-spiced-chicken-rice-60f826d2b2a8d01a500fa864-4d26d72e.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 640 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 890 mg
cuisine: Middle East
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-shawarma-spiced-chicken-rice-60f826d2b2a8d01a500fa864
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

Season all over with 1 tsp @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.
(You'll use the rest of the Shawarma Spice later.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium, preferably #nonstick pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and dice @carrots{9%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince
@garlic{1%clove}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%oz}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium-high
heat.

Add carrots in a single layer; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan with carrots; add garlic,
@jasmine rice{½%cup}, @golden raisins{1%oz}, remaining Shawarma Spice,
and ½ tsp salt. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in 1 1/2 cups water and @chicken stock concentrate{2}. Bring to a boil;
cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has reduced by half,
~{3-4%minutes}. Cover pan and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water if mixture seems dry.

Remove pan from heat; return chicken to pan. Let sit for ~{3%minutes} to
warm through.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tbsp},
@sour cream{2%tbsp}, and half the cilantro. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time
until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} to taste.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; slice crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in a big squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with chicken and garnish with
@almonds{½%oz} and remaining cilantro. Drizzle cilantro yogurt sauce over
top. Squeeze juice from any remaining lemon wedges over bowls to taste and
serve.